          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Providing Emotional Assistance with Relief and Love Act or the PEARL Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill requires U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) to establish&amp;nbsp;a pilot program to adopt dogs from local animal shelters to be trained as support dogs for CBPâ€™s Support Canine Program. Support dogs are used for grief assistance, trauma mitigation, and morale.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
